<seg id=1> The American Tennis Competition came into its third day. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, 1 September, by foreign news reporter On 31 August, The American Tennis Competition came into its third day, the last champion Sampras, who had suffered pain in his left ankle for more than one month, beat his opponent easily by 3 and 0, and qualified for the second-round men's singles. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> At present, the American contestant Sampras ranked No.1 in world tennis had not attended any competition since the middle of July. His performance this time was good. He finished the three sets all scored 6 to 2 in less than half an hour, beating the South African contestant, and he qualified for the second round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The No.8 seeded player, the Ukrainian contestant Medvediv beat his component by 6 to 3, 6 to 4, and 6 to 0, and he qualified for the second round as well. </seg>
<seg id=5> He considered it to be his 20th birthday present. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In the women's, the No.2 seeded player, Spanish Sanchez met the challenge of the French contestant N Tonga, in the end, Sanchez won by 6 to 2, 7 to 6, and she qualified for the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The No.5 seeded player, Japanese Yidagonzi, the No.9 seeded player, American M Fenlands, the 1990 champion, and Argentine Swaging, etc. all qualified for the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> According to the latest news, the American contestant Zhang Depei beat his opponent, and qualified for the third round. </seg>
</p>
